    <br>
    <!--This is colspan (Space for coloum) & Rowspan (Space for Rows)
   To manage the layout of the tables, two attributes are used, rowspan and colspan.
Attribute rowspan is used to mention the number of rows that a particular cell will
be occupying. Attribute colspan is used to mention the number of columns that a
specific cell will be occupying.
They both are used with the td tag and can also be used with the th tag.-->

    <caption> colspan and rowspan Attribute</caption>
    <table border="5">
        <tr>
        <th>coloum 1</th>
        <th colspan="2">coloum 2</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>row 4,cell 1</td>
            <td rowspan="2">row 4,cell 2</td>
            <td>row 4,cell 3</td>
            <td rowspan="2">row 4,cell 4</td>
            <td>row 4,cell 5</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>row 4,cell 1</td>
            <td rowspan="2">row 4,cell 2</td>
